The paper discusses the design and implementation of a secure and privacy-preserving identity and credential management infrastructure for vehicular communication systems. This involves aspects of cryptography, network security, and distributed systems, which are all covered by the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed system, which falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses large-scale mobility trace datasets to evaluate the proposed system, which falls under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
